definition.value: A linear amino tetrasaccharide comprising two alpha-N-glycoloylneuraminyl residues, a beta-D-galactose residue and (at the reducing end) an N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residue, linked sequentially (2->8), (2->6) and (1->4).
A N(5)-alkylglutamine where the alkyl group is isopropyl.

A branched amino oligosaccharide (tetradecasaccharide) consisting of a linear trisaccharide unit of beta-D-mannose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues, connected by (1->3) linkages, to the beta-D-mannose residue of which are linked (1->3) and (1->6) alpha-D-mannose residues, the one at O-2 being substituted at O-2 by an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl trisaccharide unit and the one at O-6 being substituted also at both O-2 and O-6 by N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl trisaccharide units.

A branched amino hexasaccharide comprising a linear tetrasaccharide chain of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residues linked sequentially (1->3), (1->4) and (1->6), to the reducing-end N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue is also linked (1->3) an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl disaccharide unit.
A N(5)-alkylglutamine obtained by formal condensation of the side-chain carboxy group of L-glutamic acid with the amino group of L-alaninol.
A member of the class of aminopyrimidine with the amino group at position 4 with additional methyl and formamidomethyl substituents at positions 2 and 5 respectively.
An amino disaccharide consisting of  N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine with an N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl residue atached at the 3-position.
A member of the class of anthracyclines that is beta-rhodomycin lacking the phenolic hydroxy group at position 11.

An amino pentasacchride comprising a chain of 3-O-sulfo-beta-D-glucuronic acid, beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose and D-glucose residues linked sequentially (1->3), (1->4), (1->3) and (1->4).
A 3beta-hydroxy steroid that is 4-pregnen-3beta-ol substituted by an oxo group at position 20.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as octanoyl.
A glyopeptide that is vancomycin in which the terminal vancosamine of the disaccharide moiety is replaced by 4-epi-vancosamine.
An indolecarboxylic acid that is indole-2-carboxylic acid in which the hydrogen at position 3 is replaced by a methyl group.
A C21-steroid in which a pregnane skeleton carries a beta-hydroxy group at position 3, an alpha-hydroxy group at position 20 and a double bond between positions 4 and 5.
An S-substituted glutathione that is glutathione in which the mercapto hydrogen has been replaced by a sulfinyl group.
A cobalt-corrinoid heptacarboxylic acid that is produced by Salmonella typhimurium.
A 2,7-dihydroxy-4'-methoxyisoflavanone in which positions 2 and 3 have R- and S-configuration respectively.
A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 9alpha-hydroxy-3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchola-1,4-dien-22-oic acid.
An amino acid zwitterion arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 2-methyl-L-tryptophan; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 9alpha-hydroxy-3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchola-4-en-22-oic acid.
A steroid acid that is 23,24-bisnor-chol-4-en-22-oic acid bearing additional oxo and hydroxy substituent at positions 3 and 9 respectively.
A steroid acid that is 23,24-bisnor-chol-1,4-dien-22-oic acid bearing an additional oxo substituent at position 3.
A steroid acid that is 23,24-bisnor-chol-1,4-dien-22-oic acid bearing additional oxo and hydroxy substituent at positions 3 and 9 respectively.
A dihydroxy monocarboxylic acid that is 2,4-dihydroxy-2,4-hexadienoic acid bearing additional methyl and oxo substituents at positions 5 and 6 respectively.
A polyunsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (9Z,12Z)-hexadeca-9,12,15-trienoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A fatty-acyl group derived from (5Z,9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadecatetraenoic acid.
A fatty-acyl group derived from (5Z,9Z,12Z)-octadecatrienoic acid.
An L-cysteine thioether in which the thiol hydrogen is replaced by a (1R,2S)-2-hydroxy-1-phosphonopropyl group
A fatty-acyl group derived from (4Z)-hexadecenoic acid.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (4Z)-hexadecenoyl.
A member of the class of phosphonic acids that is propylphosphonic acid substituted by thio and hydroxy groups at positions 1 and 2 respectively (the 1R,2S-stereoisomer)
A fatty-acyl group derived from (9Z,12E)-octadecadienoic acid
A fatty-acyl group derived from (9Z,12E)-hexadecadienoic acid
A member of the class of phosphonic acids that is propylphosphonic acid substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1 and 2 (the 1S,2S-stereoisomer).
An organophosphonate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphonate OH groups of (1S,2S)-1,2-dihydroxypropylphosphonic acid.
A hexadecenoyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (14Z)-hexadecenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A monounsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (14E)-hexadecenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

A nitrile that is acrylonitrile in which the hydrogen located beta,trans to the cyano group is replaced by a tosyl group. It is an inhibitor of cytokine-induced IkappaB-alpha phosphorylation in cells.
A fatty-acyl group derived from (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoic acid.
A ketopentose phosphate that is D-ribulose 5-phosphate in which the 1-hydroxy group is replaced by a methylthio group.
A fatty-acyl group derived from (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosapentaenoic acid.
A fatty-acyl group derived from (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoic acid.
A fatty-acyl group derived from (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosapentaenoic acid.
A 2-hydroxymyristic acid having 2R-configuration.
The (3S)-enantiomer of isoflavanone.
A member of the class of pyrimidones that is 5,6-diamino-5-[(4-hydroxyphenyl)methyl]pyrimidine-2,4-dione in which the imino hydrogen at position 6 is replaced by a D-ribityl group.
A 2-hydroxymyristic acid having 2S-configuration.
A member of the class of  flavans having one or more glycosyl residues attached at unspecified positions.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of cis-3-octenoic acid.
